{{EngvarB|date=June 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}} {{Infobox non test cricket team | name = [[Lesotho]] | image = Lesothocr.gif | caption = Flag of Lesotho | icc_member_year = 2017 | icc_status = [[ICC members|Associate member]]<ref name="Assoc">{{cite web|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/news/422449|title=Ireland and Afghanistan ICC newest full members amid wide-ranging governance reform|work=[[International Cricket Council]]|date=22 June 2017|accessdate=1 September 2018}}</ref> | icc_region = [[ICC Africa|Africa]] | captain = Motsielao Nonyane | WCL_division = n/a | regional_tournament = World Cricket League Africa Region | regional_tournament_division = Three | first_match = 10 June 2005 v [[Mozambique cricket team|Mozambique]] at [[Maseru]], Lesotho | world_ranking = not ranked | regional_ranking = 10th | asofdate = 31 July 2007}}
The '''Lesotho national cricket team''' is the team that represents the [[Kingdom of Lesotho]] in [[international cricket]]. They became an affiliate member of the [[International Cricket Council]] (ICC) in 2001<ref>[http://www.cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Countries/110.html]</ref> and an [[ICC members|associate member]] in 2017.<ref name="Assoc"/> They made their official international debut at Division Three of the Africa Region of the [[ICC World Cricket League]] in April 2006, where they came last in the eight team tournament.
In April 2018, the ICC decided to grant full [[Twenty20 International]] (T20I) status to all its members. Therefore, all [[Twenty20]] matches played between Lesotho and other [[List of International Cricket Council members|ICC members]] after 1 January 2019 will be a full T20I.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/media-releases/672322|title=All T20 matches between ICC members to get international status|work=[[International Cricket Council]]|date=26 April 2018|accessdate=1 September 2018}}</ref>
