'''FC Mashʼal-2''' ({{lang-uz|Машъал-Академия}}) is a [[Uzbekistan]]n [[association football]] club based in Mubarek. Mashʼal-2 acts as the farm club of [[Mashʼal Mubarek]]. Currently it plays in [[Uzbekistan First League|First League]].

==History==
The club was formed in 2005 under name ''Yangiyer''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcmashal.uz/ru.php/academy |script-title=ru:Футбольная академия «Машъала» |publisher=FC Mashal |language=Russian |accessdate= |date=}}</ref> Since 2010 club participates in league as ''Mashʼal Akademiya''.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.fcmashal.uz/ru.php/news/sections/academy/2729 |script-title=ru:«Машъал-Спорт» вернул прежнее название|publisher=FC Mashal|language=Russian |accessdate= |date=2010-01-22}}</ref>  Mashʼal-2 is feeder of main team. Farm clubs in Uzbekistan play in the same football pyramid as their senior team rather than a separate league. But farm teams cannot play in the same division as their senior team. Feeder teams are also permitted to participate in [[Uzbekistani Cup]].

In 2009 Mashal-2 [[2009 Uzbekistan First League|finished]] runners-up in Uzbekistan First League, but was not eligible to promote to top division as Mashʼal Mubarek was playing in [[Uzbek League]].

Formers players of Mashʼal-2 ''Ganisher Kholmurodov'' and ''Sardor Rahkmanov'' played in [[2011 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] for [[Uzbekistan national under-17 football team|Uzbekistan U-17]] team.

'''Name changes'''
* 2005: ''Yangiyer''
* 2006–2007: ''Mashʼal-2''
* 2008–2009: ''Mashʼal-Akademiya''
* 2009: ''Mashʼal-Sport''
* 2010–2013: ''Mashʼal-Akademiya''
* 2014: ''Mashʼal-2''

